# Olivetti M20 FUZIX Port — TODO

## Done
  - Kernel boots, mounts root filesystem, starts /init
  - exec binary loading (syscall_exec32.c + coff2aout + plt_relocate)
  - crt0, FUZIX libc, syscall wrappers for Z8001
  - /init with fork/exec/waitpid loop
  - V7 shell (/bin/sh) boots with prompt, builtins, error messages
  - dofork, switchin/switchout, signal delivery (VDSO unwind)
  - TTY serial driver (i8251A) with input polling from timer interrupt
  - HD driver (BIOS disk_io)
  - coff2aout: R_IMM32 + R_IMM32_NORELAX relocations with addends

## Next: build userland utilities
  - echo, cat, ls, cp, mv, rm, mkdir, chmod, etc.
  - Build from Applications/V7/cmd and/or Applications/util
  - Add to filesystem image via ucp
  - Set up PATH in init's environment

## Important: drivers
  - Floppy driver — same BIOS disk_io interface as HD
  - Video console — MC6845 framebuffer at segment 3
  - Keyboard USART — i8251A at 0xA1/0xA3 with M20 keyboard protocol

## Important: memory management
  - Multi-segment user processes (use seg A/C/D/E for larger programs)
  - Per-segment allocation instead of single flat pool

## Compiler/toolchain bugs
  - WORD_REGISTER_OPERATIONS: FIXED in gcc
  - Jump table codegen: FIXED — CASE_VECTOR_MODE HImode
  - addr(Rn) register: FIXED — use low word of pair
  - Register global asm("r10"): WORKAROUND — -ffixed-r10
  - z8k-coff-ld -r addend bug: FIXED in binutils (r_offset was dropped)
  - coff2aout addend bug: FIXED (now reads r_offset field)
  - Need to run GCC torture tests to find more bugs

## Nice to have
  - RTC / timekeeping
  - Printer driver (i8255A parallel port)
  - Proper build system integration (make from Kernel/ root)
  - Read-write filesystem mount
